about.description:
A Python implementation of the SCRAM authentication protocol defined by
RFC 5802 and RFC 7677.
about.summary: A pure-Python implementation of the SCRAM authentication protocol

name: scramp
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "scramp" %}
{% set version = "1.1.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: b57eb0ae2f9240b15b5d0dab2ea8e40b43eef13ac66d3f627a79ef85a6da0927

build:
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  noarch: python

requirements:
  host:
    - python >3.5
    - pip
  run:
    - python >3.5

test:
  imports:
    - scramp

about:
  home: https://github.com/tlocke/scramp
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: A pure-Python implementation of the SCRAM authentication protocol
  description: |
    A Python implementation of the SCRAM authentication protocol defined by
    RFC 5802 and RFC 7677.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - nicolas-geniteau
    - maximerihouey
    - ncolomer
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.15
